---
title: Oven-Baked Chicken Legs with Mac ’n’ Cheese, Broccoli, and Ranch Spice
description: Crispy breaded chicken. Mac ’n’ cheese. Easy-peasy broccoli. Need we say more about this unstoppable trifecta? Probably not, but we could go on and on about how it’s worth the effort. The chicken is about as crisp as can be thanks to a seasoned panko breadcrumb coating. It only gets better when you move on to the pasta, which is extra rich thanks to a bit of sour cream. After steaming the broccoli in the microwave and dividing everything between plates, add the magic finishing touch: a drizzle of spicy honey.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/oven-baked-chicken-legs-75b2283e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/oven-baked-chicken-legs-5af4562330006c43ad7d49a2-a4ca6102.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/oven-baked-chicken-legs-5af4562330006c43ad7d49a2
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: North America
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 980 kcal
  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 73 g
  sugar: 16 g
  protein: 48 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 520 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat the #oven{} to 450 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with aluminum foil and brush with a drizzle of @olive oil{1/2%tbsp}. Bring a #medium pot{} of salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add @Gemelli pasta{6%oz} and cook until al dente ~{10-12%minutes}. Drain and set aside.

Meanwhile, mix @Dijon mustard{2%tsp}, @sour cream{2%tbsp}, half the @ranch spice{1%tbsp}, and @milk{1%tbsp} in a shallow #dish{} (save the rest of everything). In another shallow dish, mix remaining ranch spice and @panko breadcrumbs{1.5%cup}. Place @flour{2%tbsp} (we sent more), @paprika{1%tsp}, @salt and @pepper in a large, #zip-close bag{}. Add @chicken legs{32%oz} to bag and shake to coat.

Working one piece at a time, coat chicken all over in sour cream mixture, then add to dish with panko and coat all over in crumbs, pressing to adhere. Transfer to lined baking sheet, arranging skin-side up, and sprinkle with a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tbsp}. Bake in oven until crumbs are golden brown and meat is cooked through, ~{35-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating greens and whites. In a small #bowl{}, stir together @honey{1%oz} and @hot sauce{1%tsp}. Season with @salt and set aside. 5-8 minutes before chicken is done, place @butter{1%tbsp} and scallion whites in #pot{} used for pasta. Heat over medium-high heat. Once scallions are softened, about ~{1%minute} later, add rest of @flour{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt and @pepper. Cook, stirring, for about ~{30%seconds}.

Whisk rest of @milk{5.75%oz} into pot and bring to a boil. Let bubble until thickened, about ~{2%minutes}. Whisk in @Monterey Jack cheese{1/2%cup} and remaining @sour cream{2%tbsp}. Stir in gemelli. Season with @salt and @pepper. Place @broccoli florets{16%oz} and @water{2%tbsp} in a #microwave-safe bowl{}. Cover with #plastic wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave on high until tender, about ~{3%minutes}. Drain and toss with @butter{2%tbsp}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Divide chicken, pasta, and broccoli between plates. Sprinkle with the scallion greens. Drizzle chicken with honey mixture and serve.